idyll.

idyll is an idyllic region within your computer's memory where fractals are bound to coexist in complete peace and harmony.

classes:
	main.cpp -> argument registration.
	math.cpp -> implement math methods and structures.
	frac.cpp -> implement DE's, space folds, rotations and coloring methods.
	seed.cpp -> seed generation class definition.
	math.h -> declare math functions and structures as externals in a namespace
	frac.h -> declare fractal's functions as extrenals in a namespace
	seed.h -> seed generation class declaration.

arguments:
	-h -> help. display info about the other commands.
	-x -> set width of the desired output resolution.
	-y -> set height of the desired output resolution.
